When an undefined property error occurs, theORQL highlights the problematic line of code, explains the likely cause (e.g., missing prop validation or uninitialized state), and suggests a patch. For example, if a component fails due to an undefined `user.name` property, theORQL might suggest:

jsx
// Before (failing):
function UserProfile({ user }) {
  return <h1>{user.name}</h1>;
}

// After (patched with optional chaining or default props):
function UserProfile({ user }) {
  return <h1>{user?.name || 'Guest'}</h1>;
}


The patch can be synced directly to VS Code, eliminating manual copy-pasting.
